---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="The Foundations — Trinity Files"
  description="A handful of arguments come up again and again across the verse files. Rather than answer each from scratch in every study, they are answered once here, in full."
>
  <div class="tr-wrap">
    <div class="found-page">
      <div class="found-inner">

        <a class="found-back" href="/trinity/files">&larr; Back to Trinity Files</a>

        <p class="found-eyebrow">&#8213; The Foundations &#8213;</p>
        <h1 class="found-h1">The Foundations</h1>
        <p class="found-intro">A handful of arguments come up again and again across the verse files — the same grammar, the same swap, the same scene, pressed into service for one verse after another.</p>
        <p class="found-intro plain">Rather than answer each from scratch in every study, they are answered once here, in full. Read these, and many of the verse files fall open on their own.</p>

        <div class="found-divider"></div>

        <ol class="found-ledger">

          <a class="found-row" href="/foundations/restoring-the-name">
            <span class="found-num">I</span>
            <span>
              <h3 class="found-title">Restoring the Name</h3>
              <p class="found-desc">Where your Bible prints "LORD," the manuscript says Yahuah — and what that one swap quietly buried.</p>
            </span>
            <span class="found-meta">
              <span class="found-tally">Cited by <b>6</b> studies</span>
              <span class="found-read">Read &rarr;</span>
            </span>
          </a>

          <a class="found-row" href="/foundations/us-passages">
            <span class="found-num">II</span>
            <span>
              <h3 class="found-title">The "Us" Passages</h3>
              <p class="found-desc">Why a plural form — a verb, a cohortative, or the word Elohim — names no plural God.</p>
            </span>
            <span class="found-meta">
              <span class="found-tally">Cited by <b>8</b> studies</span>
              <span class="found-read">Read &rarr;</span>
            </span>
          </a>

          <a class="found-row" href="/foundations/granville-sharp-rule">
            <span class="found-num">III</span>
            <span>
              <h3 class="found-title">The Granville Sharp Rule</h3>
              <p class="found-desc">The one-article "God and Savior" grammar — a man's rule, its real limits, and what it cannot prove.</p>
            </span>
            <span class="found-meta">
              <span class="found-tally">Cited by <b>3</b> studies</span>
              <span class="found-read">Read &rarr;</span>
            </span>
          </a>

          <div class="found-row is-soon">
            <span class="found-num">IV</span>
            <span>
              <h3 class="found-title">I AM (egō eimi)</h3>
              <p class="found-desc">The "I am" sayings — ordinary Greek self-identification, not a claim to the divine Name.</p>
            </span>
            <span class="found-meta"><span class="found-soon">In progress &middot; 6 verses</span></span>
          </div>

          <div class="found-row is-soon">
            <span class="found-num">V</span>
            <span>
              <h3 class="found-title">Worship &amp; the Throne of the Lamb</h3>
              <p class="found-desc">The shared-throne scenes in Revelation — honor flowing through the Lamb to the One on the throne.</p>
            </span>
            <span class="found-meta"><span class="found-soon">In progress &middot; 6 verses</span></span>
          </div>

        </ol>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .tr-wrap {
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, #0e0904 0%, #1a1208 20%, #160f07 100%);
    color: #f0e0bf;
    font-family: 'Crimson Pro', 'Crimson Text', Georgia, serif;
    min-height: 80vh;
  }

  .found-page {
    padding: 54px 32px 80px;
    -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
  }
  .found-inner { max-width: 980px; margin: 0 auto; }

  /* ── header ── */
  .found-back {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #8a6028;
    text-decoration: none;
    margin-bottom: 46px;
    transition: color 0.2s ease;
  }
  .found-back:hover { color: #c4a46b; }
  .found-back:focus-visible { outline: 2px solid #8a6028; outline-offset: 3px; }

  .found-eyebrow {
    text-align: center;
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 4px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #8a6028;
    margin: 0 0 16px;
  }

  .found-h1 {
    text-align: center;
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 5.5vw, 3.6rem);
    line-height: 1.1;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    color: #f0e0bf;
    margin: 0 0 28px;
  }

  .found-intro {
    max-width: 620px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    text-align: center;
    font-family: 'Crimson Pro', 'Crimson Text', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    font-style: italic;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: #c4a46b;
  }
  .found-intro.plain {
    font-style: normal;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: #dcc99a;
    margin-top: 18px;
  }

  .found-divider {
    height: 1px;
    background: #3a2510;
    max-width: 980px;
    margin: 54px auto 6px;
  }

  /* ── ledger ── */
  .found-ledger {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    border-top: 1px solid #2e1f0d;
  }

  .found-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 74px 1fr auto;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: 0 28px;
    padding: 26px 14px 24px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #2e1f0d;
    text-decoration: none;
    color: inherit;
    position: relative;
    transition: background-color 0.35s ease;
  }
  .found-row::after {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    bottom: -1px;
    height: 1px;
    width: 0;
    background: linear-gradient(90deg, #8a6028, transparent);
    transition: width 0.45s ease;
  }
  .found-row:hover { background: rgba(138, 96, 40, 0.06); }
  .found-row:hover::after { width: 100%; }
  .found-row:focus-visible { outline: 2px solid #8a6028; outline-offset: -2px; }

  .found-num {
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: 32px;
    line-height: 1;
    color: #8a6028;
    opacity: 0.62;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    transition: opacity 0.35s ease;
  }
  .found-row:hover .found-num { opacity: 1; }

  .found-title {
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: clamp(1.2rem, 2.4vw, 1.55rem);
    line-height: 1.15;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    color: #f0e0bf;
    margin: 0 0 7px;
  }

  .found-desc {
    font-family: 'Crimson Pro', 'Crimson Text', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: #b09060;
    margin: 0;
    max-width: 46ch;
  }

  .found-meta {
    text-align: right;
    align-self: center;
    white-space: nowrap;
    padding-top: 4px;
  }

  .found-tally {
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #8a6028;
  }
  .found-tally b { font-weight: 700; color: #c4a46b; }

  .found-read {
    display: block;
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #dcc99a;
    margin-top: 9px;
    transition: transform 0.35s ease, color 0.35s ease;
  }
  .found-row:hover .found-read { color: #f0e0bf; transform: translateX(5px); }

  .found-row.is-soon { cursor: default; }
  .found-row.is-soon .found-num,
  .found-row.is-soon .found-title { opacity: 0.5; }
  .found-row.is-soon .found-desc { opacity: 0.7; }
  .found-row.is-soon:hover { background: transparent; }
  .found-row.is-soon:hover::after { width: 0; }

  .found-soon {
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #7a5520;
  }

  @media (max-width: 680px) {
    .found-page { padding: 40px 20px 56px; }
    .found-row { grid-template-columns: 48px 1fr; gap: 4px 18px; }
    .found-num { font-size: 26px; }
    .found-meta { grid-column: 2; text-align: left; margin-top: 12px; }
    .found-read { margin-top: 6px; }
  }

  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    .found-row, .found-row::after, .found-num, .found-read, .found-back { transition: none; }
  }
</style>
